               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18690111-name-133" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18690111-name-133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18690111-name-133" type="surname" value="WRIGHT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18690111-name-133" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WRIGHT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cart minder—on 1st January I was employed by Mr. Elvidge to mind his cart—a little after 7 o'clock I saw the prisoner walking up and down, looking about—he came up to the horse, took off the nose—bag and threw it into the cart, and then took off the cloth and threw that into the cart—he then took the horse by the rein and led him away in the direction of Holborn—when he had got about fifteen yards, or a little more, I went up and stopped him, called a constable, and gave him into custody—I asked him where he was going—he said he was going to take the horse and cart round the corner—the cart had fifty stone of meat in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> About what time did you see me with the horse and cart! <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> About 6.50, it was dark, not pitch dark—I was standing oppo<lb></lb>site the nose bag did not fall off—I saw you take it off, and the cloth also—you were leading it away in the direction of Holborn when I stopped you.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
