                  </hi>. I am a butcher, of 102, Seymour-street, Euston-square—on the morning of the 1st January I left my horse and cart in care of Wright while I went into the market, with fifty stone of meat in it—I don't know the prisoner—I never gave him authority to move my cart—the cart cost me 61<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and the meat 15<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.,</p>
